Architecture description language

Architecture description languages (ADLs) are used in several disciplines: system engineering, software engineering, 
and enterprise modelling and engineering.

The system engineering community uses an architecture description language as a language and/or a conceptual model to 
describe and represent system architectures.

http://byadl.di.univaq.it/index.html
http://byadl.di.univaq.it/byadl.html


